requestBody.query: what should i know about credit scores

200.answer: Your credit score is a number that reflects the information in your credit report. Your credit report is a record of your credit history. It includes information about whether you pay your bills on time and how much you owe to creditors. Your credit score can change, depending on how your credit history changes. The range of scores ranges from a low of 300 to a high of 850. Generally, the higher your score, the more likely you are to be offered better credit terms.

A credit term is the length of time you have to repay a loan or credit card balance. It can also refer to the interest rate you will be charged on the loan or credit card.
